oke—have converged with a radical economic and social agenda to shape daily life in the United States, especially by enshrining the male-dominated white family as the ideal of national identity. Through insightful observation and critical dissection, Ventura and Chan paint a striking portrait of how these forces enable each other, perpetuating social injustice and inequity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNeoliberalismzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aWhite nationalismzUnited Statesy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aalt right.  aamerican democracy.  abooks for classes about racism.  aethnonationalist.  afree markets.  ainsurrection.  aneoliberal economies.  apatriarchal family.  apolitical violence.  aprivilege.  aracial capitalism.  aracial neoliberalism.  aracism.  aviolence of white power.  awhite supremacy.1 aChan, Edward K, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520392809?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520392809423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520392809/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131925-4  EBOOK 